{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ffb71cfc-5eb8-4b26-969d-8eecb0bfe91f","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package (ships with xUnit.net 2.9.3+):\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable** Microsoft.Testing.Platform in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained apps).\n\n**Optional:** Add `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` if you want `dotnet test` to use the new platform runner by default (otherwise it bridges through VSTest compatibility).\n\nThat's the core migration — swap the runner package and add the MSBuild property.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d45c983f-aff5-45e3-b60e-b1fced890709","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":341,"requestId":"E847:1242BB:27C30BF:2A3534C:6A0493AB"},"id":"fb85b586-3ecd-494f-a7a7-40d1a9bf99e2","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:07:34.363Z","parentId":"489237ea-7fa7-49a0-ae1b-35c52c9a082a"}
